<TITLE> Three RU teachers sent to jail </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Rajshahi, Sept 1 (bdnews24.com)  A Rajshahi court Saturday ordered the three detained Rajshahi University teachers to jail, after eight days in remand. Court inspector Mahbubul Quddus Siddiqui told bdnews24.com: "After interrogation the three teachers were sent to jail by the metropolitan magistrate's court (Rajshahi). I have heard that the chargesheet against them is almost ready." Security forces arrested former RU vice-chancellor Saidur Rahman Khan, Progressive Teachers Community convener Abdus Sobhan and associate professor of management Moloy Kumar Bhowmik on Aug 24, following the protests on campus. The case against them was filed under the emergency powers rules on Aug 25, when they were given 10-day remand. But they were kept in custody for eight days. According to newspaper reports, during their remand the three teachers were taken to Dhaka and interrogated in the joint interrogation cell. Motihar police sub-inspector Farukh Hossain, who filed the case, told bdnews24.com: "Preparations for submitting the chargesheet are almost completed. They will be charged with violations of emergency powers rules." The case in question accused a total of 2,500 people in connection with the student protests at Rajshahi University. Apart from the three detained teachers, only 30 other individualsteachers and students of the universityhave reportedly been named in the chargesheet. bdnews24.co
